'''Alderaan Ruge Liqueur''' was an [[Alcohol/Legends|alcoholic]] [[Foodstuff/Legends|drink]] that shared its name with [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]],<ref name="Art of Betrayal">{{WEGCite|story=The Art of Betrayal|book=The Politics of Contraband}}</ref> a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] that was [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destroyed]] by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] using the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star's]] [[Superlaser/Legends|superlaser]].<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref> During the [[New Republic era]], the [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] [[Gangster/Legends|gangster]] [[Marg Sonat]] hired a crew to smuggle a crate from [[Rantine Space Station/Legends|Rantine Space Station]] to [[Kwenn Space Station/Legends|Kwenn Space Station]]. Among its contents were three bottles of the very rare [[Liqueur/Legends|liqueur]] that were each worth about 350 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]].<ref name="Art of Betrayal" />

However, the liqueur and other luxury items were only decoys to distract Imperial [[Customs Inspector|customs inspectors]] like [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Tenric]] from noticing the true treasure: a protoype [[Personal energy shield/Legends|personal energy shield]] that [[Crime lord/Legends|crimelord]] [[Sard Nightbringer]] intended to sell at an auction on the ''[[Stellar Mermaid]]''.<ref name="Art of Betrayal" />

